[01:46.15]	On abjects, orts and imitations,
[01:48.43]	Which, out of use and staled by other men,
[01:51.32]	Begin his fashion: do not talk of him,
[01:53.97]	But as a property. And now, Octavius,
[01:56.49]	Listen great things:--Brutus and Cassius
[01:59.26]	Are levying powers: we must straight make head:
